e"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlginaA='u miDomaAru Al$~iEori", "text_ar": "الغِنَا=ءُ مِضْمَارُ الشِّعْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  [app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Singing is that in which the excellences of poetry are displayed, like as the excellences of a horse are displayed in the hippodrome"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "time, of forty days, during which a horse is reduced to food barely sufficient to sustain him, after his having been fed with fodder so that he has become fat;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA;) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "time during which a horse is thus prepared for racing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for an expedition against the enemy:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. as above. (TA.) It is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aaloyawoma miDomaArN wagadFA", "text_ar": "اَلْيَوْمَ مِضْمَارٌ وَغَدًا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@los~ibaAqu waAls~aAbiqu mano sabaqa A@lojan~apa", "text_ar": "ا@لْسِّبَاقُ وَالسَّابِقُ مَنْ سَبَقَ ا@لْجَنَّةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "To-day is a time for training, and to-morrow is the race, and the winner is he who wins Paradise:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] i. e., to-day one is to work, in the present world, for the desire of Paradise; like as a horse is trained for racing. (Sh.) [One of the explanations of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmDmAr", "text_ar": "المضمار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the K is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaAyapu Alfarasi fiY Als~ibaAqi", "text_ar": "غَايَةُ الفَرَسِ فِى السِّبَاقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or, as in the TA,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lils~ibaAqi", "text_ar": "لِلسِّبَاقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The goal,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {